<subSubSection id="6CD9657DFFB667315BE5CE428AAF209E" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="186" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="247C36F6FFB667315BE5CE428FFF2032" blockId="3.[151,1437,1803,2015]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,153,935]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="186" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB667365BE5CE428F1B251B" bold="true" box="[199,322,1839,1866]" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB6673659A8CE5D8DCB251B" authority="Swinhoe, 1912" authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1912" box="[650,914,1839,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Spialia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB6673659A8CE5D8C80251B" box="[650,729,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">Spialia</emphasis>
Swinhoe, 1912
</taxonomicName>
, where these species were placed previously. Keys to 5, 15, 21 (exclude antithesis of 25), or thesis 
<quantity id="E33B9B13FFB6673659D5CE398D69253C" box="[759,816,1875,1902]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" unit="in" value="11.0">11 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="40524B07FFB66736581ACE3E8A5D253F" author="de Jong, R." box="[824,1028,1875,1902]" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" pagination="23 - 146" refId="ref8814" refString="de Jong, R. (1978) Monograph of the genus Spialia Swinhoe (Lepidoptera, Hesperiidae). Tijdschrift voor entomologie, 121, 23 - 146." type="journal article" year="1978">de Jong (1978: 28</bibRefCitation>
&amp; 30), constituting his 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB667365E30CE398B38253F" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1875" box="[1298,1377,1876,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colotes">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB667365E30CE398B38253F" box="[1298,1377,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">colotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB667365E53CE398E8225C0" authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delagoae">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB667365E53CE398E8225C0" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">delagoae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB667365A3CCE158F2825C3" baseAuthorityName="Plotz" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[286,369,1912,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ernsta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dromus">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB667365A3CCE158F2825C3" box="[286,369,1912,1938]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">dromus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species groups. Differs from its relatives by the following characters. Ventral hindwing with straight median white band not separated into sports, i.e., white spot in cell RS-M 
<subScript id="B84734B3FFB667365F05CEC08A7625EA" attach="left" box="[1063,1071,1965,1979]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">1</subScript>
(space 6) joins central spot (discal cell) to the outer (and not inner) spot in cell Sc+ 
<collectionCode id="42D2AE33FFB6673659F4CEAD8CB3258B" box="[726,746,1984,2010]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="B84734B3FFB6673659C8CEBC8CAB258E" attach="left" box="[746,754,2001,2015]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">1</subScript>
-RS (space 7), but in many species of 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB667365FB8CEAD8AB0258B" authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1912" box="[1178,1257,1984,2010]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Spialia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="185" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB667365FB8CEAD8AB0258B" box="[1178,1257,1984,2010]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="185">Spialia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this band either broken into spots or directed basad at costa. While 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB1673159FDC9F48D7722E2" authorityName="Swinhoe" authorityYear="1912" box="[735,814,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Spialia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB1673159FDC9F48D7722E2" box="[735,814,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Spialia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species lack costal fold in males, some 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB167315FDAC9F78B1A22E2" authority="Zhang &amp; Brockmann &amp; Cong &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin, 2020" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Brockmann &amp; Cong &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" authorityYear="2020" box="[1272,1347,154,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ernsta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB167315FDAC9F78B1A22E2" box="[1272,1347,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Ernsta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species have costal fold (
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB167315A78C9D08FF02286" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1875" box="[346,425,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colotes">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB167315A78C9D08FF02286" box="[346,425,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">colotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group). Species with costal fold are in addition characterized by the central white discal cell spot on dorsal forewing not closer to discocellular spot than to the basal cell spot and no two white spots are present above over the central cell spot (to distinguish from 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB16731587CC8688D9E234E" baseAuthorityName="Trimen" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[862,967,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Agyllia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asterodia">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB16731587CC8688D9E234E" box="[862,967,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">asterodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group of 
<bibRefCitation id="40524B07FFB167315FA8C8688B6B234E" author="de Jong, R." box="[1162,1330,261,287]" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" pagination="23 - 146" refId="ref8814" refString="de Jong, R. (1978) Monograph of the genus Spialia Swinhoe (Lepidoptera, Hesperiidae). Tijdschrift voor entomologie, 121, 23 - 146." type="journal article" year="1978">de Jong (1978)</bibRefCitation>
that does not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB167315A15C8478FDB2312" authority="Zhang &amp; Brockmann &amp; Cong &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin, 2020" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Brockmann &amp; Cong &amp; Shen &amp; Grishin" authorityYear="2020" box="[311,386,298,323]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ernsta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB167315A15C8478FDB2312" box="[311,386,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Ernsta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and hindwing submarginal pale spots in cells M 
<subScript id="B84734B3FFB167315895C8578DE62319" attach="left" box="[951,959,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">1</subScript>
-M 
<subScript id="B84734B3FFB1673158C3C8578DB02319" attach="left" box="[993,1001,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">2</subScript>
&amp; M 
<subScript id="B84734B3FFB167315F0BC8578A682319" attach="left" box="[1065,1073,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">2</subScript>
-M 
<subScript id="B84734B3FFB167315F76C8578A052319" attach="left" box="[1108,1116,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">3</subScript>
(spaces 4 &amp; 5) offset basad from the rest of the submarginal spots. Species without costal fold either lack the basal white spots in discal cell on dorsal forewing, however, some white scales along cubital vein may be present forming a narrow streak (the 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB167315BB5C8F88EA723FE" authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1898" box="[151,254,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delagoae">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB167315BB5C8F88EA723FE" box="[151,254,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">delagoae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group), or on dorsal forewing in CuA 
<subScript id="B84734B3FFB1673159DCC8CB8D5F23E5" attach="left" box="[766,774,422,436]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">2</subScript>
-1 
<collectionCode id="42D2AE33FFB167315835C8F88D7423FE" box="[791,813,405,431]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
+2 
<collectionCode id="42D2AE33FFB16731586EC8F88D3B23FE" box="[844,866,405,431]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
cell (space 1 
<collectionCode id="42D2AE33FFB1673158D2C8F88A5F23FE" box="[1008,1030,405,431]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" type="Herbarium">B</collectionCode>
) the outer lower median spot absent and inner lower median spot not smaller than the outer upper median spot (
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB1673158F6C8D48A7E2382" baseAuthorityName="Plotz" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[980,1063,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ernsta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dromus">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB1673158F6C8D48A7E2382" box="[980,1063,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">dromus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group). In male genitalia, uncus not deeply incised, gnathos dorsally joined to tegumen, if gnathos free (in some species from the 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB167315E14C8B08BC423A6" authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1898" box="[1334,1437,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pyrgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delagoae">
