<paragraph id="247C36F6FFB167315BE5CB018AAF209E" blockId="4.[151,1437,153,935]" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis id="16B7EAE4FFB167315BE5CB018FBB20D6" bold="true" box="[199,482,620,647]" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Derivation of the name.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular. It honors Ernst Brockmann of Lich, 
<collectingCountry id="5CD47666FFB167315BD8CBFC8F3B20FA" box="[250,354,657,683]" name="Germany" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Germany</collectingCountry>
and his unstoppable passion for 
<taxonomicName id="E3C34D75FFB1673159F9CBFC8D3820FA" box="[731,865,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hesperiidae</taxonomicName>
in general and the Grizzled skippers in particular. Without his enthusiasm, help, encouragement and specimens this study would not be accomplished.
</paragraph>
